				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Evolve! The Game of Unnatural Selection" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Evolve is a 'build-your-own animal' card game for 2-6 players based on scientific principles -- perfect for gamers, families, and classrooms.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each epoch you'll mutate your creature to face one of 15 Biomes and 21 unique Challenges in your quest for dominance over your competitors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What if a meteor strikes, or an ice age overtakes the planet? Can you successfully build a nest to impress your mate, or convince those strange 2-legged creatures that you'd make a good candidate for domestication?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Based on the cards you play, creatures are rated on 4 attributes (aggression, resilience, allure, &amp;amp; gathering), and can also have over a dozen different special abilities (flying, swimming, climbing, desert survival, etc.).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Evolutionary pressure will determine how fast you can change -- a creature less well suited to its environment has all the more reason to change! And who knows how long favorable conditions will prevail? You need to strike a fine balance between dominating your competition now, and preparing for the future.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Evolve is a fast-paced card game taking 1 hour or less to play. It is fun and suitable for adults who like &amp;quot;euro-style&amp;quot; games or card games. Who doesn't want to build animals? It's also educational, and suitable as a classroom or family-style game (kids aged ~10 or younger may require guidance).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
